# EDP Billing — Alembic migrations

Schema for `workflow_properties`, `segment_execution`, and `agent_control`.

## Commands (from repo root, venv active)

```powershell
# Apply all pending migrations
.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic upgrade head

# Create a new migration after changing src/agent/edp/models.py
.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

# Show current revision
.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic current

# Roll back one revision
.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic downgrade -1
```

Database URL is read from `.env` (`DB_*` or `DATABASE_URL`) — same as the agent.

## Upgrading from pre-Alembic databases

If tables were already created by `create_all` against PostgreSQL, stamp
the current schema without re-running DDL:

```powershell
.venv\Scripts\python.exe -m alembic stamp head
```

The agent runs `upgrade head` automatically on startup.
